stylometry: Safety stock is the amount kept in stock that is of excess of what is needed to meet demand. This is important because if a company only has enough product in stock to meet the expected demand they could potentially miss out on sales if demand exceeds their expectation. Also, in addition to missing a sale they may also damage their reputation with customers since that customer will need to go eslewhere to get the product. Safety stock is also useful if there is a delay with the next shipment of inventory (perhaps a longer lead time than expected). In this way the safety stock could be used until the order arrives and all potential sales coudl be made.
